Titolo: O'Leary Manager 2000

Anno: 2000

Descrizione: O'Leary Manager 2000 is a football player-manager game by British studio LiveMedia, released in 2000 for the Game Boy Color. The player can choose whether they want to focus on the management side of football, play the matches themselves on the game's 2D match engine, or combine the two features for a more in-depth experience.  It is endorsed by Irish football manager David O'Leary, who was managing English Premier League side Leeds United at the time of the game's release. The game was released as Guy Roux Manager 2000 in France, DSF Fußball Manager in Germany, Co Adriaanse Football Manager in the Netherlands and Barça Manager 2000 in Spain.

Genere: Sport 

Valutazione: N/A
